one_reviews_text: The videos are short travel documentaries of Taiwan. They feature the Sky Lantern Festival, the Land Lantern Fesitval, and the Night Market, the last of which is the only video to feature food. They are interesting peeks into a different culture - if that's what you're looking for, then check it out!

review_title: i just want to be first that give it 5

one_reviews_text: This is a nice use of VR -- a chance to explore different cultures around the world. This takes us to three places in China and Hong Kong -- Two lantern festivals and a food market. Although the 360 degree videos lacked the sharpness of the preview images, the narration really added to the experience. Some people might complain that the sky lantern festival is not environmentally correct, but I liked it!
Images were muddy and murky, people seemed to walk into an area where they ghosted or split in half. Great idea, poor execution.
